      "message": "The function `av1_alloc_pmc()` does the allocation of `PICK_MODE_CONTEXT`. In the parent version, the caller sites of this function did not check the status of allocation and hence could result in encoder crash in case of allocation failures. In this CL, the return status of `av1_alloc_pmc()` is checked at all caller sites and `aom_internal_error()` is invoked with the correct error info in case of an allocation failure.\n\nThis change is bit-exact and has been verified using bitstream-match tests for a combination of various configuration values for --threads, --tile-rows, --tile-columns, --cpu-used, --end-usage, --row-mt, --fp-mt, etc. Validated all unit-tests with sanitizers (address and thread) and valgrind.",
